  "texts": [
    "This takes a more outcomebased stance than the transparency frameworks discussed in Sect.",
    "\"Current approaches: Process-based transparency\", where the focus is on the steps that have been taken by developers during the design of the algorithm as well as the broader socio-technical system.",
    "At the same time, it takes a broader view than the current outcome-based transparency frameworks discussed in Sect.",
    "\"Current approaches: Outcome-based transparency\", which risk reducing the provided information about a system to the accuracy and statistical fairness of the algorithm.",
    "As such, a value-based framework satisfies the three requirements on transparency that were outlined in Sect."
  ],
